Definition: the phenomenon whereby a small change at one place in a complex system can have large effects elsewhere, e.g., a butterfly flapping its wings in Rio de Janeiro might change the weather in Chicago
Synonyms: consequence, the, phenomenon, whereby, a, small, change, at, one, place, in, complex, system, can, have, large, effects, elsewhere, e, g, butterfly, flapping, its, wings, Rio, de, Janeiro, might, weather, Chicago
Category: noun.phenomenon
